The weather is
perfect today, too.

32
00:02:42,333 --> 00:02:44,083
[BOTH]
Thank you for the food.

33
00:02:44,166 --> 00:02:48,166
Hey, if you want, I can make us
dinner tonight. I don't work.

34
00:02:48,250 --> 00:02:49,500
That would be great.

35
00:02:49,583 --> 00:02:52,416
I could finish the manuscript
today! Thank you.

36
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:54,916
[RITSUKA] Aren't you translating
for a magazine this time?

37
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,041
[MARIA]
Yep. It's a British fantasy.

38
00:02:57,125 --> 00:02:58,875
[RITSUKA]
Cool.

39
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:03,708
[RITSUKA]
I'll get it.

40
00:03:05,708 --> 00:03:06,958
Good morning!

41
00:03:07,041 --> 00:03:09,291
Oh no, wait. It's more
like good evening for you.

42
00:03:09,375 --> 00:03:10,750
How's London? Having fun?

43
00:03:10,833 --> 00:03:12,375
Oh, it's Lindo!

44
00:03:12,458 --> 00:03:14,500
Yeah. I'm doing fine.

45
00:03:14,583 --> 00:03:17,083
Here, I'll let you talk to Mom.

46
00:03:20,666 --> 00:03:22,166
Bye, Mom. Happy writing!

47
00:03:22,250 --> 00:03:23,625
[MARIA]
Wait. It's Monday.

48
00:03:23,708 --> 00:03:24,541
Don't leave yet.

49
00:03:24,625 --> 00:03:25,916
[gasps]

50
00:03:29,291 --> 00:03:30,458
There we go!

51
00:03:30,541 --> 00:03:31,875
You never forget.

52
00:03:31,958 --> 00:03:33,541
It's actually kind of adorable.

53
00:03:33,625 --> 00:03:35,958
You're so serious about
these little charms.

54
00:03:36,041 --> 00:03:37,541
Not just adorable.

55
00:03:37,625 --> 00:03:38,750
They're much more.

56
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:40,833
These Charms keep you
safe and protected.

57
00:03:40,916 --> 00:03:42,041
Yes. I know.

58
00:03:42,125 --> 00:03:43,333
Uh!

59
00:03:44,541 --> 00:03:46,416
Have a great day.

60
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:48,166
[RITSUKA]
Uh...

61
00:03:54,833 --> 00:03:57,208
See you after school!

62
