♪ and they'd turn and smile,
it beings... ♪

76
00:04:58,833 --> 00:05:03,791
♪ A new world around
the corner, in the wind ♪

77
00:05:11,166 --> 00:05:14,583
[AZUNA]
Ritsuka! Hey, what's up?

78
00:05:14,666 --> 00:05:17,208
Hi, Azuna. Nothing much.

79
00:05:17,916 --> 00:05:20,875
So overachiever, did you
finish that English paper?

80
00:05:20,958 --> 00:05:23,083
Yep. One perk of having
a writer for a mom.

81
00:05:23,166 --> 00:05:25,666
[AZUNA] So unfair!
Will you help me, then?

82
00:05:25,750 --> 00:05:27,083
There you are!

83
00:05:27,166 --> 00:05:28,125
[RITSUKA, AZUNA]
Uh?

84
00:05:28,208 --> 00:05:29,708
[STUDENT 1C]
Girl, what did you do?

85
00:05:29,791 --> 00:05:30,458
Uh...?

86
00:05:30,541 --> 00:05:31,666
[AZUNA]
Hm?

87
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:35,541
What?! But why?!

88
00:05:35,625 --> 00:05:37,833
What could the student
council president want?!

89
00:05:37,916 --> 00:05:39,416
It's so weird.

90
00:05:39,500 --> 00:05:41,458
[AZUNA] Come on, you have
to know what this is about.

91
00:05:41,541 --> 00:05:44,291
[RITSUKA] I don't, though.
I swear. I have no idea.

92
00:05:44,375 --> 00:05:45,541
You sure?

93
00:05:45,625 --> 00:05:47,916
The Great Rem doesn't
summon for no reason.

94
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:49,416
You must have done something.

95
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:52,750
I haven't done anything.
You know me!

96
00:05:52,833 --> 00:05:54,000
[STUDENT 1D]
That her?

97
00:05:54,083 --> 00:05:55,416
[STUDENT 1AA]
Sure is. I wonder what she did.

98
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:56,791
[STUDENT 1BB] She doesn't
look like the rebel type.

99
00:05:56,875 --> 00:05:58,708
[STUDENT 1E] Is it weird
that I'm kinda jealous?

100
00:05:58,791 --> 00:06:00,125
[STUDENT 1F]
I know!

101
00:06:00,208 --> 00:06:01,416
[STUDENT 1E] She gets one-on-one
time with the Great Rem.

102
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:02,541
[STUDENT 1F]
I'd get in trouble too

103
00:06:02,625 --> 00:06:04,083
if it means going to
the third library.

104
00:06:04,166 --> 00:06:07,958
Hey, you're gonna
be okay. Don't freak.

105
00:06:08,041 --> 00:06:12,375
[RITSUKA] No. I know. It's just
a meeting; no big deal.

106
00:06:19,416 --> 00:06:21,958
Third library, here I come.

107
00:06:25,458 --> 00:06:30,416
♪ ♪

108
00:06:35,708 --> 00:06:37,458
♪ Why don't you
give up now? ♪

109
00:06:37,541 --> 00:06:39,125
♪ You know it's checkmate ♪

110
00:06:39,208 --> 00:06:41,458
♪ It's time for you
to confess and... ♪

111
00:06:41,541 --> 00:06:42,875
[ALL]
♪ ...say yes! ♪

112
00:06:42,958 --> 00:06:45,791
♪ Just follow me you lovely
little butterflies ♪

113
00:06:45,875 --> 00:06:47,541
♪ I'll enchant you
with a whisper ♪

114
00:06:47,625 --> 00:06:49,416
[ALL]
♪ We love your sweet soul! ♪

115
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:52,833
♪ Give into your desires
and be all mine ♪

116
00:06:52,916 --> 00:06:55,083
♪ Let me take you
in my arms and... ♪

117
00:06:55,166 --> 00:06:56,708
[ALL]
♪ ...and kiss you! ♪

118
00:06:56,791 --> 00:07:01,666
♪ Oh, so innocent, I might break
you, but I'll be as gentle ♪

119
00:07:01,750 --> 00:07:03,250
♪ as one like me can... ♪

120
00:07:03,333 --> 00:07:08,083
[ALL] ♪ Bow down and
worship at our feet ♪

121
00:07:08,166 --> 00:07:09,541
[SHIKI] ♪ The hearts
within everyone... ♪

122
00:07:09,625 --> 00:07:11,458
[MAGE]
♪ ...will be stolen ♪

123
00:07:11,541 --> 00:07:12,916
[URIE]
♪ And to the ends of the earth ♪

124
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,291
[REM]
♪ They all will fall ♪

125
00:07:14,375 --> 00:07:15,958
[MAGE, SHIKI]
♪ Oh so charmingly ♪

126
00:07:16,041 --> 00:07:17,583
[REM, URIE]
♪ And so tenderly ♪

127
00:07:17,666 --> 00:07:23,125
[ALL] ♪ It's a labyrinth
of depravity ♪

128
00:07:23,208 --> 00:07:26,458
♪ We're those in
the third library ♪

129
00:07:26,541 --> 00:07:29,958
♪ Shiko Academy's
student council ♪

130
00:07:30,041 --> 00:07:33,125
♪ Blessings we will give, to all
those those who come to us ♪

131
00:07:33,208 --> 00:07:36,833
♪ Upon them, we
bestow our seal ♪

132
00:07:36,916 --> 00:07:40,041
♪ the forbidden flower garden ♪

133
00:07:40,125 --> 00:07:43,541
♪ Shiko Academy's
student council ♪

134
00:07:43,625 --> 00:07:46,500
♪ There is no use.
Don't run from us now ♪

135
00:07:46,583 --> 00:07:50,041
♪ You're a captive
of our charms ♪

136
00:08:03,166 --> 00:08:04,541
[RITSUKA]
Uh...

137
00:08:13,375 --> 00:08:14,458
[REM]
Ritsuka Tachibana?

138
00:08:14,541 --> 00:08:17,041
Uh! Yes. That's me.

139
00:08:17,125 --> 00:08:18,333
Rem Kaginuki.

140
00:08:18,416 --> 00:08:20,666
President of Shiko Academy's
Student Council.

141
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:23,375
Glad you were able
to meet with us.

142
00:08:24,791 --> 00:08:27,750
[REM] Though, I wish it were
under better circumstances.

143
00:08:27,833 --> 00:08:31,083
We've received word that you've
been violating school policies.

144
00:08:31,166 --> 00:08:32,708
[RITSUKA]
What?! I haven't!

145
00:08:32,791 --> 00:08:35,166
There must be some mistake!

146
00:08:35,250 --> 00:08:38,750
Yet this note says otherwise.
You deny it?

147
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:39,833
You bet I do!

148
00:08:39,916 --> 00:08:41,583
I've never broken
a rule in my life.

149
00:08:41,666 --> 00:08:46,625
Who wrote that note anyway?
And what does it say I did?!

150
00:08:46,708 --> 00:08:50,708
I will be the one asking
the questions. Understand?

151
00:08:50,791 --> 00:08:52,875
You should at least
let me defend myself.

152
00:08:52,958 --> 00:08:56,375
Watch out. This one talks back.
She's got a mind of her own.

153
00:08:56,458 --> 00:08:58,541
This got interesting!

154
00:08:58,625 --> 00:09:01,125
Not to mention exciting.

155
00:09:01,208 --> 00:09:03,166
You're very intriguing.

156
00:09:03,250 --> 00:09:05,375
You're not like the
other girls, are you?

157
00:09:05,458 --> 00:09:06,791
[gasps]

158
00:09:38,791 --> 00:09:40,625
To tell you the truth,

159
00:09:40,708 --> 00:09:44,125
I summoned you for my own
selfish curiosity.

160
00:09:57,375 --> 00:10:00,458
[REM inahles]

161
00:10:00,958 --> 00:10:02,625
[REM grunting]

162
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:09,250
[ALL grunt]

163
00:10:14,291 --> 00:10:15,625
Uh!

164
00:10:19,333 --> 00:10:20,833
Not sure what I was saying,

165
00:10:20,916 --> 00:10:23,541
but whatever you think
you found out is wrong.

166
00:10:23,625 --> 00:10:25,958
Now, if you'll excuse me.

167
00:10:28,250 --> 00:10:29,458
[door slams]

168
00:10:29,541 --> 00:10:32,458
Wasn't that strange?
With the pendant, I mean.

169
00:10:32,541 --> 00:10:35,500
It's incredible how
clueless she really is.

170
00:10:35,583 --> 00:10:37,208
The poor little thing.

171
00:10:37,291 --> 00:10:41,041
She might be a little more of a
challenge than we thought. Fun.

172
00:10:41,125 --> 00:10:43,500
[REM]
She won't be a problem.

173
00:10:48,666 --> 00:10:52,333
Don't worry.
Next time is checkmate.

174
00:10:56,041 --> 00:10:58,458
Well, that was really weird.

175
00:10:58,541 --> 00:10:59,250
[sighs]

176
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:00,958
[AZUNA]
Ritsuka!

177
00:11:01,041 --> 00:11:02,291
[RITSUKA]
Oh, hi, Azuna.

178
00:11:02,375 --> 00:11:03,791
[AZUNA]
You have to tell me everything.

179
00:11:03,875 --> 00:11:05,375
[RITSUKA]
It was ridiculous.

180
00:11:05,458 --> 00:11:07,916
They were getting on to me for
no reason about breaking rules.

181
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,958
[AZUNA scoffs]
That's, like, insane.

182
00:11:10,041 --> 00:11:13,250
[RITSUKA] Everybody thinks the
"Great Rem" is just so perfect.

183
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:14,875
But the truth is
he's a total jerk.

184
00:11:14,958 --> 00:11:16,541
[AZUNA]
But everything's okay, right?

185
00:11:16,625 --> 00:11:17,833
I mean you don't
have to go back?

186
00:11:17,916 --> 00:11:20,208
[RITSUKA] Trust me.
That's never gonna happen.

187
00:11:20,291 --> 00:11:23,458
Hmph! Let's go.

188
00:12:05,250 --> 00:12:06,791
[gasps]

189
00:12:12,125 --> 00:12:13,375
[gasps]

190
00:12:16,791 --> 00:12:19,125
[RITSUKA]
Who did this?

191
00:12:27,500 --> 00:12:28,125
[gasps]

192
00:12:28,208 --> 00:12:34,041
[MAN humming]

193
00:12:37,458 --> 00:12:40,250
[RITSUKA gasping]

194
00:12:42,250 --> 00:12:45,000
I think it's in a back room.

195
00:12:55,125 --> 00:12:56,875
[MARIA]
Ritsuka!

196
00:12:56,958 --> 00:12:58,750
[gasping]

197
00:13:00,625 --> 00:13:01,916
[whimpers]

198
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:04,291
Mom, no!

199
00:13:04,375 --> 00:13:05,875
[MARIA]
Don't!

200
00:13:19,250 --> 00:13:22,125
Quick, just call the police.

201
00:13:25,208 --> 00:13:26,625
[RITSUKA]
What?

202
00:13:34,791 --> 00:13:37,333
[POLICE 1A]
What's the problem here?

203
00:13:37,416 --> 00:13:40,500
But how...?

204
00:13:40,583 --> 00:13:41,750
No way...

205
00:13:41,833 --> 00:13:44,333
Based on your report,
I expected some damage.

206
00:13:44,416 --> 00:13:46,333
[RITSUKA]
There was!

207
00:13:54,291 --> 00:13:56,583
[POLICE 1A] Everything looks
to be in order to me, ma'am.

208
00:13:56,666 --> 00:13:58,583
Didn't you claim your mother
was attacked, too?

209
00:13:58,666 --> 00:14:03,041
[RITSUKA] Yes! The room was
a mess... and my mom... was...

210
00:14:09,458 --> 00:14:12,083
[RITSUKA]
I just... I don't understand.

211
00:14:12,166 --> 00:14:13,916
[POLICE 1A] It's quite
the interesting situation,

212
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:15,416
that's for sure.

213
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:17,458
[POLICE 1B] The good news is
everything seems to be okay.

214
00:14:17,541 --> 00:14:18,666
[RITSUKA]
What about my mom?

215
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:20,250
[POLICE 1A]
She's probably running errands.

216
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:22,500
[RITSUKA] That can't be it!
She was bleeding!

217
00:14:22,583 --> 00:14:24,000
[POLICE 1B]
Look kid,

218
00:14:24,083 --> 00:14:25,958
how about you contact us again
if she doesn't come back.

219
00:14:26,041 --> 00:14:28,666
[RITSUKA]
No, please! Wait!

220
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:30,416
Don't go...

221
00:14:34,125 --> 00:14:35,458
[exhales]

222
00:14:42,083 --> 00:14:46,416
[phone rings]

223
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:47,500
[gasps] Mom, are you--

224
00:14:47,583 --> 00:14:49,000
[OPERATOR]
The number you have dialed

225
00:14:49,083 --> 00:14:53,041
is currently unavailable.
Please hang up and try again.

226
00:14:58,583 --> 00:15:02,833
Oh god, I think those
men... took her.

227
00:15:07,375 --> 00:15:09,958
[phone rings]

228
00:15:10,041 --> 00:15:13,000
[LINDO]
Hey, Ritsuka. What's up?

229
00:15:13,083 --> 00:15:14,083
It's Mom!

230
00:15:14,166 --> 00:15:15,916
[LINDO]
Mom? What's wrong?

231
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:17,708
They took her!

232
00:15:21,791 --> 00:15:24,625
[LINDO]
I'm on my way. Listen carefully.

233
00:15:24,708 --> 00:15:26,875
I need you to stay at
Azuna's until I get there.

234
00:15:26,958 --> 00:15:27,708
Do you understand?

235
00:15:27,791 --> 00:15:30,250
[RITSUKA]
Uh! Yeah. But...

236
00:15:30,333 --> 00:15:32,708
What if Mom shows up here?
She might need me.

237
00:15:32,791 --> 00:15:33,958
It's not safe.

238
00:15:34,041 --> 00:15:37,583
Whoever kidnapped her,
they may be coming back.

239
00:15:37,666 --> 00:15:38,833
And please,

240
00:15:38,916 --> 00:15:41,166
you must always remember
to wear your pendant.

241
00:15:41,250 --> 00:15:42,750
What?

242
00:15:52,958 --> 00:15:55,791
[phone rings]

243
00:15:55,875 --> 00:15:57,791
Perfect timing.

244
00:16:00,166 --> 00:16:03,583
[AZUNA] Um, that's super scary.
Get over here, stat!

245
00:16:03,666 --> 00:16:05,375
Do you want me to come get you?

246
00:16:05,458 --> 00:16:07,416
[RITSUKA]
No, I'll be okay.

247
00:16:27,583 --> 00:16:28,666
[gasps]

248
00:16:32,458 --> 00:16:34,375
You guys were in my house.

249
00:16:34,458 --> 00:16:39,041
Where is she? My mom.
What did you do with her?!

250
00:16:45,708 --> 00:16:47,125
[whimpers]

251
00:16:47,666 --> 00:16:49,375
[JEK]
Hmm...

252
00:16:52,500 --> 00:16:54,791
Where is the forbidden grimoire?

253
00:16:54,875 --> 00:16:56,708
Tell me.

254
00:16:56,791 --> 00:16:58,916
Now.

255
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:02,416
[RITSUKA whimpers]
Ow, stop!

256
00:17:03,625 --> 00:17:05,208
That's odd.

257
00:17:08,833 --> 00:17:12,416
Damn it, vervain!

258
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:14,625
[RITSUKA whimpers]

259
00:17:17,583 --> 00:17:20,791
I suggest you let her go.

260
00:17:20,875 --> 00:17:23,125
Well that's not gonna happen.

261
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:24,291
[RITSUKA gasps]

262
00:17:25,083 --> 00:17:27,750
[VAMPIRES growling]

263
00:17:31,125 --> 00:17:33,416
[RITSUKA]
What is going on?

264
00:17:36,916 --> 00:17:37,708
[chuckles]

265
00:17:37,791 --> 00:17:39,791
[VAMPIRE 1A groans]

266
00:17:48,375 --> 00:17:49,791
[VAMPIRES grunt]

267
00:17:52,583 --> 00:17:55,291
[VAMPIRES groaning]

268
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:09,291
[gasps] Oh, Rem; it's you.

269
00:18:09,375 --> 00:18:13,291
Don't worry about them.
They won't be back.

270
00:18:13,375 --> 00:18:19,791
[RITSUKA]
Uh... Um. Thank you for that.

271
00:18:19,875 --> 00:18:23,416
You, uh, saved me.

272
00:18:29,750 --> 00:18:32,208
What? What's wrong?

273
00:18:34,416 --> 00:18:37,583
Nothing. It's not you.

274
00:18:37,666 --> 00:18:40,083
[exhales]

275
00:18:40,166 --> 00:18:41,833
It's your scent.

276
00:18:41,916 --> 00:18:43,375
[gasps]

277
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:51,291
[car door opens]

278
00:19:01,583 --> 00:19:04,958
[RITSUKA] I don't even know
what's real anymore.

279
00:19:05,041 --> 00:19:07,291
When I got back, it looked
like nothing happened.

280
00:19:07,375 --> 00:19:08,875
The police thought
I made it all up

281
00:19:08,958 --> 00:19:12,041
and didn't seem worried
that my mom was gone.

282
00:19:12,125 --> 00:19:13,625
Those were the guys that did it.

283
00:19:13,708 --> 00:19:16,833
I swear I saw them there.
They broke in and took my mom.

284
00:19:16,916 --> 00:19:19,958
But why? What could they
have possibly wanted?

285
00:19:20,041 --> 00:19:21,708
Not sure.

286
00:19:21,791 --> 00:19:23,916
They did mention something
to me about looking for

287
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,833
a forbidden grimoire.

288
00:19:25,916 --> 00:19:28,000
Do you even know
what a grimoire is?

289
00:19:28,083 --> 00:19:31,958
[RITSUKA] Sort of.
It's a book of magic, isn't it?

290
00:19:32,041 --> 00:19:33,916
I don't get why they'd ask me.

291
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:36,583
I'm not an expert on that stuff.

292
00:19:36,666 --> 00:19:39,250
Well, you've at least heard
of a grimoire before.

293
00:19:39,333 --> 00:19:41,625
Do you know anything else?

294
00:19:41,708 --> 00:19:43,291
Yeah, I guess a little bit.

295
00:19:43,375 --> 00:19:46,375
My grandfather
studied ethnology.

296
00:19:46,458 --> 00:19:49,208
When he was alive, he'd research
all these old stories

297
00:19:49,291 --> 00:19:52,500
about demons and vampires
and black magic in Europe.

298
00:19:52,583 --> 00:19:55,708
He did share some of
what he knew with me.

299
00:19:59,416 --> 00:20:02,083
[BUTLER 1A]
Welcome home, Master Rem.

300
00:20:08,166 --> 00:20:10,333
[REM]
I don't mean to alarm you,

301
00:20:10,416 --> 00:20:12,458
but I think all these
events are related.

302
00:20:12,541 --> 00:20:15,750
Your house being attacked,
your mother disappearing,

303
00:20:15,833 --> 00:20:17,833
and then there are the incidents
we're currently dealing with

304
00:20:17,916 --> 00:20:19,583
at the Academy.

305
00:20:19,666 --> 00:20:23,125
[RITSUKA]
What kind of incidents?

306
00:20:23,208 --> 00:20:24,750
It would seem
that Shiko Academy

307
00:20:24,833 --> 00:20:27,000
is housing a group of
devil worshippers.

308
00:20:27,083 --> 00:20:28,875
You can't be serious?

309
00:20:28,958 --> 00:20:31,125
And, curiously, the note
the Council received

310
00:20:31,208 --> 00:20:32,500
said that you were involved.

311
00:20:32,583 --> 00:20:34,166
No way. It's not true.

312
00:20:34,250 --> 00:20:35,833
I'm not part of
anything like that.

313
00:20:35,916 --> 00:20:37,750
[REM]
These men seem to disagree.

314
00:20:37,833 --> 00:20:40,750
I suspect they think you
are hiding the grimoire.

315
00:20:40,833 --> 00:20:42,125
[RITSUKA]
I'm not!

316
00:20:42,208 --> 00:20:46,041
I already told you,
I don't know anything about it.

317
00:20:46,125 --> 00:20:48,166
Sorry. I'm upset.

318
00:20:48,250 --> 00:20:51,833
My mom's been missing for hours.
I'm worried. I should go.

319
00:20:51,916 --> 00:20:54,875
Maybe now the police
will believe me.

320
00:20:54,958 --> 00:20:56,375
I'll call them on your behalf.

321
00:20:56,458 --> 00:20:57,125
[RITSUKA gasps]

322
00:20:57,208 --> 00:20:58,541
They'll listen to me.

323
00:20:58,625 --> 00:21:01,958
The authorities greatly
respect the Kaginuki name.

324
00:21:04,958 --> 00:21:06,500
[RITSUKA]
Wait.

325
00:21:06,583 --> 00:21:08,708
Thank you so much for this, Rem.

326
00:21:08,791 --> 00:21:10,541
I'm not sure why you're helping,

327
00:21:10,625 --> 00:21:13,333
but I truly
appreciate everything.

328
00:21:14,583 --> 00:21:15,958
[gasps]

329
00:21:16,041 --> 00:21:20,041
Don't get the wrong idea.
I'm not doing this for you.

330
00:21:20,125 --> 00:21:21,750
As Student Council President,

331
00:21:21,833 --> 00:21:25,208
it is my responsibility
to maintain order.

332
00:21:26,875 --> 00:21:29,125
[door creaks, slams]

333
00:21:33,666 --> 00:21:34,458
[dog barks]

334
00:21:34,541 --> 00:21:35,791
[gasps]

335
00:21:39,625 --> 00:21:41,916
Now, where did you come from?

336
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,416
[barks]

337
00:21:43,500 --> 00:21:45,916
So cute.

338
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:47,750
[RITSUKA laughs]

339
00:23:32,750 --> 00:23:34,333
[REM]
So you're familiar with it?

340
00:23:34,416 --> 00:23:36,958
[RITSUKA]
My grandpa's house is there.

341
00:23:37,041 --> 00:23:40,458
This is her phone! That means
she's been in the house!

342
00:23:40,541 --> 00:23:42,541
[REM]
We'll call this checkmate.

343
00:23:42,625 --> 00:23:45,875
Act Two: "Jitterbug of
Doubts and Secrets."

